  <part id="gdv">
    <title>LibGdv Overview and introduction</title>
    <para>
      The GDV-library tries to provide a simple data-visualization-library in 
      the gtk+-framework. It is the attempt to use the powerful programming-features 
      of the glib- and gtk+-libraries such as object-oriented programming, 
      theme-settings by CSS-files, referencing, introspection and widget-based geometry 
      management in a professional data-visualization-library. It works 
      on many UNIX-like platforms, as well as Windows and OS X. LibGDV is released 
      under the terms and conditions of the GNU Lesser General Public License (GNU LGPL).
    </para>
